	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Aug 8th 12:58 PM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=14401><span id= >Quaras</span></a><br><span id=notbold>5 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Actually, Wu's Fighting Armor trivials around 158 in tailoring.&nbsp;&nbsp;The Wu's Fighting Gauntlets (which were the first piece of tailored Wu Armor created ) do trivial around 88, but the remaining pieces range from 131 to 158.<br><br>The easiest way to get Wu's Armor is to go to East Karanas and try to get as much spider silk as you can carry.  Any tailor worth his salt would be thrilled to trade you armor for raw materials as the Wu's Armor is the only way to get to 158 currently.  For further information on the trivial levels on this stuff, check out www.eqtraders.com.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
