	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=5982&mid=99425757050139>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=5982&mid=99425757050139>making Wu's clothing</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=5982&mid=99425757050139#post><img src=/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11"></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Wed, Jul 4th 10:39 AM 2001</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span><br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Wu's clothing has a trivial lvl of 88 in tailoring. But is NOT cheap to make. You have to get an Enchanter to make the Viscous Mana to make this armor. The cheapest I have bought the mana was 25pp a pop so you want to make sure your tailoring skill is up there because you'll cry having failures. to make the Wu's fighting guantlets you need..1 glove pattern...1 silk swatch...1 greater lightstone...1 vial of viscous mana...and 4 heady kiolas.{ Master brewer made..trivial at 135}..guants are AC4..weight 0.1 and are a light source..Good lucky</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
